<!-- Problem -->
<section class="s" id="problem">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="s-intro">
      <div class="kick">The problem</div>
      <h2>You have 60 internal tools. Your engineers <em>know</em> three.</h2>
      <p>Platform teams spend their days context-switching across IAM, CI, Vault, Datadog, PagerDuty, and whatever home-grown scripts survived the last reorg. Tickets pile up. Runbooks rot. The people closest to the problem can't reach the tool that would fix it.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="pain">
      <div class="pcol">
        <div class="n">01 · THE ENGINEER</div>
        <div class="quote">"Who has the runbook for rotating the Stripe key? Is it in Notion or Confluence?"</div>
        <div class="who">— product engineer, 10pm Thursday</div>
        <div class="gap"></div>
        <div class="break"><b>What's broken.</b> The tool exists. The access exists. The knowledge of where both live doesn't.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="pcol">
        <div class="n">02 · THE PLATFORM LEAD</div>
        <div class="quote">"My team is a human router. We're the bottleneck on every bucket, every grant, every rotation."</div>
        <div class="who">— head of platform engineering</div>
        <div class="gap"></div>
        <div class="break"><b>What's broken.</b> Work that belongs to self-service gets routed through Slack DMs and on-call rotations.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="pcol">
        <div class="n">03 · THE AUDITOR</div>
        <div class="quote">"Show me who created this resource, why, and which policy approved it — before 5pm."</div>
        <div class="who">— compliance &amp; security</div>
        <div class="gap"></div>
        <div class="break"><b>What's broken.</b> Action and audit live in different systems. Nobody trusts the chain of custody.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- How it works -->
<section class="s" id="how" style="background:var(--surface-2); border-top:1px solid var(--line); border-bottom:1px solid var(--line);">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="s-intro">
      <div class="kick">How it works</div>
      <h2>From prompt to approved action — in <em>three</em> moves.</h2>
      <p>AskGenie pairs an orchestrator agent with GenieLamps — small, governed wrappers around your existing tools. The agent understands intent. The lamp owns the action. The bridge enforces policy.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="how">
      <div class="step">
        <div class="num">01</div>
        <h3>Ask in plain English</h3>
        <p>Anyone on your team can describe what they need. The orchestrator matches intent to the right lamp, surfaces it, and pre-fills what it already knows.</p>
        <div class="viz">
          <div class="line"><span class="k">query</span><span class="v">"make an s3 bucket for analytics"</span></div>
          <div class="line ok"><span class="k">match</span><span class="v">aws-storage · 0.94</span></div>
          <div class="line"><span class="k">account</span><span class="v">prod-us-east-1</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="num">02</div>
        <h3>Review, don't rewrite</h3>
        <p>A real UI renders on the canvas — not a wall of JSON. Fields are pre-filled with context; you only change what's different.</p>
        <div class="viz">
          <span class="pill">PRE-FILLED</span>
          <div class="form-mini">
            <div class="row"><span class="lbl">name</span><span class="val">acme-analytics-nightly-exports</span></div>
            <div class="row hl"><span class="lbl">region</span><span class="val">us-east-1</span></div>
            <div class="row"><span class="lbl">sse</span><span class="val">kms · acme-data-platform</span></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="num">03</div>
        <h3>Run with guardrails</h3>
        <p>Every action flows through the Application Bridge. Approvals route by policy. Audit is automatic. No blind writes.</p>
        <div class="viz">
          <div class="line"><span class="k">policy</span><span class="v">prod.create-resource</span></div>
          <div class="line"><span class="k">approver</span><span class="v">jordan.park</span></div>
          <div class="line ok"><span class="k">audit</span><span class="v">logged · trace 01JD9Y…</span></div>
          <div class="bars">
            <span style="height:40%"></span><span style="height:70%"></span><span style="height:55%"></span>
            <span style="height:80%"></span><span style="height:62%"></span><span style="height:90%"></span>
            <span style="height:50%"></span><span style="height:75%"></span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Marketplace preview -->
