<!-- Security -->
<section class="s" id="security" style="background:var(--surface-2); border-top:1px solid var(--line); border-bottom:1px solid var(--line);">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="s-intro">
      <div class="kick">Security &amp; governance</div>
      <h2>An agent you can put in production. <em>Actually.</em></h2>
      <p>Every prompt and every action flows through a dedicated Application Bridge. The agent doesn't hold your credentials — your IAM does. The cockpit never ships a write that can't be traced.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="sec">
      <div class="sec-list">
        <div class="sec-item">
          <div class="ico">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="3" y="11" width="18" height="11" rx="2"></rect><path d="M7 11V7a5 5 0 0 1 10 0v4"></path></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4>Zero trust by default</h4>
            <p>Lamps assume short-lived IAM roles per run. No long-lived keys in the agent. Every call is scoped to the user's policy — not the agent's.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="sec-item">
          <div class="ico">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M20 6 9 17l-5-5"></path></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4>Policy-routed approvals</h4>
            <p>Write policy once; the bridge enforces it across every lamp. Production resource? Routes to on-call. Sensitive secret? Requires two approvers. Non-prod read? Just runs.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="sec-item">
          <div class="ico">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V8z"></path><path d="M14 2v6h6"></path><path d="M9 13h6M9 17h4"></path></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4>Immutable audit</h4>
            <p>Prompt, reasoning, parameters, diff, approver, outcome — all captured as one trace. Stream it to your SIEM. Prove what happened to any auditor in one query.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="sec-item">
          <div class="ico">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 2 2 7l10 5 10-5z"></path><path d="M2 17l10 5 10-5"></path><path d="M2 12l10 5 10-5"></path></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h4>Self-hosted or SaaS</h4>
            <p>Deploy the bridge in your VPC. The model never sees your data plane — only the intent and the lamp's structured response. Works on-prem.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="sec-vis">
        <div style="font-family:var(--f-mono); font-size:11px; color:var(--mute); text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:.08em; margin-bottom:12px;">RUN · 01JD9Y7B6N · "create s3 bucket for analytics"</div>
        <div class="trace ok">
          <div class="t">Intent matched</div>
          <div class="d"><code>lamp</code>aws-storage.create_bucket · 0.94</div>
        </div>
        <div class="trace ok">
          <div class="t">Policy evaluated</div>
          <div class="d"><code>policy</code>prod.create-resource · requires approval</div>
        </div>
        <div class="trace ok">
          <div class="t">Approver notified</div>
          <div class="d"><code>slack</code>#platform-approvals · jordan.park · 3s</div>
        </div>
        <div class="trace">
          <div class="t">Pending approval</div>
          <div class="d"><code>sla</code>&lt; 5 min · auto-escalate to @platform-leads</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

